President Obama announced his intention to nominate Meredith Attwell Baker as Commissioner for the Federal Communications Commission (FCC). Baker has over twelve years of experience in telecommunications and technology policy, both in the public and private sector. She previously served as Acting Assistant Secretary of the National Telecommunications and Information Administration and has held various positions focusing on telecommunications, intellectual property, and international trade issues. Baker earned a Bachelor of Arts degree from Washington & Lee University and a law degree from the University of Houston. She is a member of the Texas State Bar.